{0 Hover}

Show the link target on hover so the user can preview where a link
points without navigating.

{1 Input}

A cursor position (0-based line and character) in a markdown file that
belongs to a vault with a built index.

{1 Link detection}

Same link forms as {!page-"feature-go-to-definition"}: wikilinks,
markdown links, markdown images.  External URLs are excluded.

{1 Response}

If the cursor falls on a recognized, resolved link, return a
[textDocument/hover] response:

{t
  | Field          | Value                                            |
  |----------------|--------------------------------------------------|
  | contents       | Markdown string (see below)                      |
  | range          | byte range of the link                           |
}

{2 Contents format}

{ul
  {- {b Resolved note link}: the resolved relative path, e.g.
     [folder/note.md].  If a heading or block-ID fragment is present,
     append it: [folder/note.md#section-one].}
  {- {b Resolved embed link}: same as note link, prefixed with
     ["Embed: "].}
  {- {b Unresolved link}: ["Unresolved: target"].}
}

{1 Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b Cursor outside any link}: no hover result.}
  {- {b Multi-target ambiguity}: show the first candidate path and
     note the number of candidates, e.g.
     ["folder/note.md (1 of 2 matches)"].}
}
